col_mapping = {
     'Weighted_Distribution' : 'Weighted_Distribution'
}

data.rename(columns=col_mapping, inplace=True)

# setting Weighted_Distribution_Promo and TDP to Weighted_Distribution(w)
data['Weighted_Distribution_Promo'] = data['Weighted_Distribution']
data['TDP'] = data['Weighted_Distribution']
data['ACV'] = data['ACV_Weighted_Distribution']

# Extract required columns
reqCols_unilever = ['country', 'category', 'company', "spf_desc", "Sales_Volume","Sales_Value",'Sales_Units','ACV',"Weighted_Distribution","Weighted_Distribution_Promo",'Number_of_Stores_in_Universe','Numeric_Distribution(w)','TDP', 'year', 'week','date']
reqCols_comp = ['country', 'category', 'company', "product_desc", "Sales_Volume","Sales_Value",'Sales_Units','ACV',"Weighted_Distribution","Weighted_Distribution_Promo",'Number_of_Stores_in_Universe','Numeric_Distribution(w)','TDP', 'year', 'week','date']

# Create two dataframes, one for uniliver and other for competition
uni_df = data[data.company=='UNILEVER'][reqCols_unilever].copy(deep=True)
comp_df = data[data.company!='UNILEVER'][reqCols_comp].copy(deep=True)

# Copy unilever df for using in for pct sales calculation
from datetime import datetime
uni_df_copy = unilever_df.copy(deep=True)

# Calculating start and end date

# Start Date
b = uni_df_copy.groupby(["spf_desc"], as_index=False) \
  .agg({'date':'max'})
startDate = b['date'].max()
startDate.to_pydatetime()
#print (startDate)

# End date will be one year from start date
endDate = datetime(startDate.year - 1, startDate.month, startDate.day)
pd.to_datetime(endDate)
print(startDate,endDate)

discontinued SPFs¶

In [0]:
# Check for discontinued SPFs for UL
spf_discontinued_list = list()
num=[12,11,10]

for spf in unilever_df.spf_desc.unique():
      for i in num:
        sorted_spf_top_52_df = unilever_df[unilever_df.spf_desc==spf].sort_values(by=['year', 'week','date'], ascending=False)[['spf_desc', 'year', 'week','date','Weighted_Distribution', 'Sales_Volume']].copy()
        sorted_spf_top_10_df = sorted_spf_top_52_df.head(i).copy()
        mean_wd_top_10 = sorted_spf_top_10_df.Weighted_Distribution.mean()

        sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume']=sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume'].shift(1)
        sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume'].iloc[0]=sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume'].iloc[0]
        sorted_spf_top_10_df['diff']=sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume']-sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume']
        #mean_svol_top_52 = sorted_spf_top_52_df.Sales_Volume.mean()
        sum_rdiff_svol_top_10 = sorted_spf_top_10_df['diff'].sum()

        if int(mean_wd_top_10) <= 5:
            if sum_rdiff_svol_top_10<=0:
                spf_discontinued_list.append(spf)
                break

print(spf_discontinued_list)

# Check for discontinued SPFs for Comp
spf_discontinued_list = list()
num=[12,11,10]

for spf in comp_df.product_desc.unique():
      for i in num:
        sorted_spf_top_52_df = comp_df[comp_df.product_desc==spf].sort_values(by=['year', 'week', 'date'], ascending=False)[['product_desc', 'year', 'week','date','Weighted_Distribution', 'Sales_Volume']].copy()
        sorted_spf_top_10_df = sorted_spf_top_52_df.head(i).copy()
        mean_wd_top_10 = sorted_spf_top_10_df.Weighted_Distribution.mean()

        sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume']=sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume'].shift(1)
        sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume'].iloc[0]=sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume'].iloc[0]
        sorted_spf_top_10_df['diff']=sorted_spf_top_10_df['shift_volume']-sorted_spf_top_10_df['Sales_Volume']
        #mean_svol_top_52 = sorted_spf_top_52_df.Sales_Volume.mean()
        sum_rdiff_svol_top_10 = sorted_spf_top_10_df['diff'].sum()

# unilever_df.fillna(0,inplace=True)

# Replace WD with TDP where mode(WD) > 85

subset_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['spf_desc','Weighted_Distribution'])
dis_spf = unilever_df['spf_desc'].unique()
unilever_df['Weighted_Distribution'] = unilever_df['Weighted_Distribution'].astype(int)
for spf in dis_spf:
    df_1= unilever_df[unilever_df['spf_desc']==spf][['spf_desc','Weighted_Distribution']].mode()
    df_1=df_1.dropna()
    subset_df=pd.concat([subset_df,df_1],ignore_index=True)

list_spf=subset_df[subset_df['Weighted_Distribution'].astype(float)>85]['spf_desc']

unilever_df.loc[unilever_df['spf_desc'].isin(list_spf),"Weighted_Distribution"]=unilever_df['TDP']

# Check for periodicity

spf_list = unilever_df['spf_desc'].unique()
spf_inco = []

import datetime
spf_inco = []
spf_details = list()
week_diff_list = []
for i in spf_list:
    print(i)
    uni_df_test = unilever_df[unilever_df['spf_desc']==i]
    min_year = np.min(uni_df_test['year'])
    min_week = np.min(uni_df_test[uni_df_test['year']==min_year]['week'])
    min_date = np.min(uni_df_test['date'])
    print(f"min_date in dataset : {min_date}")



    max_year = np.max(uni_df_test['year'])
    max_week = np.max(uni_df_test[uni_df_test['year']==max_year]['week'])
    max_date = np.max(uni_df_test['date'])
    print(f"max_date in dataset : {max_date}")


    # date of min week
    d_min = str(min_year)+"-W"+str(min_week)
    r_min = datetime.datetime.strptime(d_min + '-1', "%Y-W%W-%w")
    print(r_min)



    # date of max week
    d_max = str(max_year)+"-W"+str(max_week)
    r_max = datetime.datetime.strptime(d_max + '-1', "%Y-W%W-%w")
    print(r_max)

    # no. of weeks between two dates
    from datetime import date
    weeks = (max_date-min_date).days/7
    weeks= weeks+1
    print(weeks)


    dummy_df = uni_df_test.groupby(['spf_desc','year'], as_index=False).agg({'week':'nunique'})
    dummy_df = dummy_df.groupby(['spf_desc'], as_index=False).agg({'week':'sum'})
    print(dummy_df.loc[0, 'week'])

#   week_diff_list.append(dummy_df.loc[0, 'week'] - weeks)
    weeks_missing = weeks-dummy_df['week'][0]
    spf_name = list(dummy_df[dummy_df['week'] < weeks]['spf_desc'])
#   if(len(spf_name)!=0):
#   print(f"SPF {i} doesn't have continiuos coverage")
    if(len(spf_name)!=0):
        spf_inco.append(spf_name[0])
    spf_details.append(
    {
        'spf_desc': i,
        'min_date': min_date,
        'max_date': max_date,
        'weeks_total': weeks,
        'weeks_missing': weeks_missing
     })



print(spf_inco)



try :
    if len(spf_inco)>0:
        raise Exception("Data is incomplete for the above spfs")
except Exception as error:
    print(error)

Feature generation¶

Average Price¶

  • value/Volume
In [0]:
unilever_df['TDP_points'] = unilever_df['Numeric_Distribution(w)'] * 100
unilever_df['ROS_calc'] = unilever_df['Sales_Value'] / (unilever_df['TDP_points']*unilever_df['Number_of_Stores_in_Universe'])

unilever_df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], 0, inplace=True)

comp_df['TDP_points'] = comp_df['Numeric_Distribution(w)'] * 100
comp_df['ROS_calc'] = unilever_df['Sales_Value'] / (comp_df['TDP_points']*comp_df['Number_of_Stores_in_Universe'])

comp_df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], 0, inplace=True)
In [0]:
unilever_df['Avg_Price'] = unilever_df.Sales_Value / unilever_df.Sales_Volume
comp_df['Avg_Price'] = comp_df.Sales_Value / comp_df.Sales_Volume

Base Price¶

  • We have weekly data
  • Max average price on rolling window of last 7 weeks
In [0]:
unilever_df["Base_Price"] = unilever_df.groupby(['spf_desc']).Avg_Price.apply(lambda x: x.rolling(window=7,min_periods=1).max())
comp_df["Base_Price"] = comp_df.groupby(['product_desc']).Avg_Price.apply(lambda x: x.rolling(window=7,min_periods=1).max())
In [0]:
RM_window=12
  
#forward 12 weeks
unilever_df['Base_Units_Price1']=unilever_df.groupby('spf_desc').Avg_Price.apply(lambda x:x.rolling(window=RM_window).max())

unilever_df['Base_Units_Price1']=unilever_df.groupby('spf_desc').Base_Units_Price1.fillna(method='bfill')
  
#backward 12 weeks
unilever_df['Base_Units_Price2']=unilever_df.groupby('spf_desc').Avg_Price.apply(lambda x:x.rolling(window=RM_window).max().shift(-(RM_window-1)))

unilever_df['Base_Units_Price2']=unilever_df.groupby('spf_desc').Base_Units_Price2.fillna(method='ffill')
  
unilever_df['Base_Units_Price']=unilever_df['Base_Units_Price2']
  
unilever_df.loc[unilever_df['Base_Units_Price1']<unilever_df['Base_Units_Price2'],'Base_Units_Price']=unilever_df['Base_Units_Price1']
unilever_df=unilever_df.drop(['Base_Units_Price1','Base_Units_Price2'],axis=1)

new=pd.DataFrame()

for j in unilever_df['spf_desc'].unique():
#     print(j)
    temp=unilever_df.loc[unilever_df['spf_desc']==j]
    temp=temp.reset_index(drop=True)
    bp = temp['Base_Units_Price'].values.tolist()
    ap = temp['Avg_Price'].values.tolist()
    bp_n = temp['Base_Units_Price'].values.tolist()
    for i in range (1,len(bp)):
        if(bp[i]>bp_n[i-1])&(bp[i]>ap[i]):
        bp_n[i] = max(bp_n[i-1],ap[i])
    temp['Base_Units_Price'] = bp_n
    new=pd.concat([new,temp],axis=0,sort=True)

TPR¶

  • Avg price / base price
In [0]:
unilever_df['TPR'] = (1- unilever_df['Avg_Price']/unilever_df['Base_Price'])*100
comp_df['TPR'] = (1- comp_df['Avg_Price']/comp_df['Base_Price'])*100

Avg items¶

  • TDP / ACV
In [0]:
unilever_df['Avg_items'] = unilever_df['TDP'] / unilever_df['ACV']
comp_df['Avg_items'] = comp_df['TDP'] / comp_df['ACV']

Unit_Size¶

  • Sales Volume / Sales Units
In [0]:
unilever_df['Unit_Size'] = unilever_df.Sales_Volume / unilever_df.Sales_Units
comp_df['Unit_Size'] = comp_df.Sales_Volume / comp_df.Sales_Units

Identify product format for unilever and competitor and get market share¶

In [0]:
consolidated_data = pd.concat([
  unilever_df.rename(columns={'spf_desc': 'product'}),
  comp_df.rename(columns={'product_desc': 'product'})
])

In [0]:
# Aggregate by product
consolidated_data_by_product = consolidated_data.groupby(['country', 'category', 'company', 'product'], as_index=False).agg({'Sales_Volume':'sum'})

# Get market share
consolidated_data_by_product['MS'] = (consolidated_data_by_product['Sales_Volume']/consolidated_data_by_product['Sales_Volume'].sum()) * 100

# Add rolling MS to identify top 90% contributing products
consolidated_data_by_product = consolidated_data_by_product.sort_values(by=['MS'], ascending=False)
consolidated_data_by_product['cml_MS'] = consolidated_data_by_product['MS'].cumsum()

product_cont_threshold = 90
consolidated_data_by_product['satisfy_threshold'] = consolidated_data_by_product['cml_MS'].apply(lambda x: 1 if int(x) <= product_cont_threshold else 0)
consolidated_data_by_product.head()

Seasonality¶

In [0]:
def calc_mat_year(df):  
  mat_year = []
  n = int(len(df)/52)
  sub_df = df.tail(52)
  mat_year = [sub_df['date'].dt.year.max()]*52
  for i in range(2,n+1):
    sub_df = df.tail(52*i).head(52)
    mat_year = [sub_df['date'].dt.year.max()]*52 + mat_year
  mat_year = [df.head(len(df)-(n*52))['date'].dt.year.max()]*(len(df)-(n*52)) + mat_year
#   print(mat_year)
  return mat_year

# calculate MAT week
unilever_df = unilever_df.reset_index().join(unilever_df.groupby(['spf_desc']).apply(lambda grp: list(range(1,53))[-(len(grp)-(int(len(grp)/52)*52)):]+list(range(1,53))*int(len(grp)/52)).to_frame().rename(columns={0:'mat_week'}).explode('mat_week').reset_index().drop('spf_desc', axis=1)).drop('index', axis=1)

# calculate MAT year
unilever_df = unilever_df.reset_index().join(unilever_df.groupby(['spf_desc']).apply(lambda grp: calc_mat_year(grp)).to_frame().rename(columns={0:'mat_year'}).explode('mat_year').reset_index().drop('spf_desc', axis=1)).drop('index', axis=1)

# calculate MAT yearly avg. Sales Volume
unilever_df['Sales_Volume_mat_yr_avg'] = unilever_df.groupby(['spf_desc','mat_year'])['Sales_Volume'].transform('mean')

# calculate Index
unilever_df['Index'] = unilever_df['Sales_Volume']/unilever_df['Sales_Volume_mat_yr_avg']

# calculate Seasonality based on last 3 years
# unilever_final_df = pd.merge(unilever_final_df,
# unilever_final_df.groupby('spf_desc').apply(lambda grp: grp.tail(int(len(grp)/52)*52)).reset_index(drop=True).groupby(['spf_desc','mat_week'])['Index'].mean().to_frame().rename(columns={'Index':'Seasonality'}).reset_index(), on=['spf_desc','mat_week'])
unilever_df = pd.merge(unilever_df,
unilever_df.groupby('spf_desc').apply(lambda grp: grp.sort_values(by=['date']).tail(3*52)).reset_index(drop=True).groupby(['spf_desc','mat_week'])['Index'].mean().to_frame().rename(columns={'Index':'Seasonality'}).reset_index(), on=['spf_desc','mat_week'])

# calculate Seasonality based on last 2 years

Regression to identify competitors¶

In [0]:
# spf_debug_list=[]

Method 2¶

In [0]:
import statsmodels.api as sm
from scipy.stats import pearsonr
from copy import deepcopy
import math

# Extract internal and external competiton superset
comp_supersets = {
  'internal': consolidated_data_by_product[(consolidated_data_by_product.satisfy_threshold==1) &
                                           (consolidated_data_by_product.company=='UNILEVER')]['product'].unique().tolist(),
  'external': consolidated_data_by_product[(consolidated_data_by_product.satisfy_threshold==1) &
                                           (consolidated_data_by_product.company!='UNILEVER')]['product'].unique().tolist()
}


# Initialize comp tracker master DFs
int_comp_tracker_master_df = pd.DataFrame()
ext_comp_tracker_master_df = pd.DataFrame()

# Store the spf specific dataframe to dictionary
spf_dataframe_dict = dict()

# Store the non-UL products dataframe to dictionary
comp_prod_dataframe_dict = dict()

all_ul_spfs = unilever_df.spf_desc.unique()

for spf in all_ul_spfs:
  spf_dataframe_dict[spf] = unilever_df[unilever_df.spf_desc==spf].copy(deep=True)

for comp_prod in comp_df.product_desc.unique():
  comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod] = comp_df[comp_df.product_desc==comp_prod].copy(deep=True)
  comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod]['year']=comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod]['year'].astype(int)
  comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod]['week']=comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod]['week'].astype(int)

# Print logs for these SPFs
spf_logs = [] 

# Identifying internal competitors
for target_spf in spf_dataframe_dict:
  print(f"\n\nTarget SPF: {target_spf}")
  
  ########################################## Internal competition identification ########################################
  temp_tgt_spf = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][['year', 'week', 'Sales_Volume']].copy(deep=True)
  
  
  # Track correlation 
  corr_tracker = list()
  
  # For OLS, we need num_obs > num_features, hence we will restrict num features to be 80% of observations. We will pick top 80% based on market share
  int_comp_superset = comp_supersets['internal']
  int_comps_for_stage_1 = min(len(int_comp_superset), int(len(temp_tgt_spf) * 0.4)) # 40% because we regress both on price and WD
  
  for i, comp_spf in enumerate(int_comp_superset[:int_comps_for_stage_1]):
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(spf_dataframe_dict[comp_spf][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price', 'Weighted_Distribution']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
      .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}',
                       'Weighted_Distribution': f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_spf}'})
    
    # Calculate correlation (to be used as last step to shortlist)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_spf}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    corr, _ = pearsonr(temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'], temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'])
    corr_tracker.append({
      'spf': comp_spf,
      'corr': corr
    }) 
    
    # Take log of the prices
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_spf}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_spf}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    #spf_list[i+1] = comp_spf # counter starts from 1 to account for constant term later on
    
  # Take log of Sales Volume
  temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'] = temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x==0 else np.log(x))
  temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.rename(columns={'Sales_Volume': 'log_Sales_Volume'})
  
  # Regress on the logged comp prices to predict logged sales volume
  X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
  Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
  X = sm.add_constant(X)
  ic_ols_fit = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
  
  # Create spf-wise p-values for both Avg price and WD
  spf_tracker_internal = list()
  for col_index in range(1, len(X.columns)):
    temp_spf_details = dict()
    cspf_name = X.columns[col_index]
    if 'Avg_Price' in cspf_name:
      temp_spf_details['spf_name'] = cspf_name[14:]
      temp_spf_details['p_value_avg_price'] = ic_ols_fit.pvalues[col_index]
      temp_spf_details['coeff_avg_price'] = ic_ols_fit.params[col_index]
    elif 'Weighted_Distribution' in cspf_name:
      temp_spf_details['spf_name'] = cspf_name[26:]
      temp_spf_details['p_value_WD'] = ic_ols_fit.pvalues[col_index]
      temp_spf_details['coeff_WD'] = ic_ols_fit.params[col_index]
    spf_tracker_internal.append(deepcopy(temp_spf_details))
  
  spf_tracker_internal_df = pd.DataFrame(spf_tracker_internal)
  spf_tracker_internal_df.insert(0, 'target_spf', target_spf)
  spf_tracker_internal_df = spf_tracker_internal_df.groupby(['target_spf', 'spf_name'], as_index=False).sum()
  
  # Track intermediate shortlisted spfs  
  intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price = spf_tracker_internal_df[(spf_tracker_internal_df['p_value_avg_price'] < 0.05) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['spf_name'] != target_spf) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['coeff_avg_price'] > 0)].spf_name.tolist()
  
  # pick the ones with p-value more than or equal to 0.05 but with +ve coeff
  intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price_rem = spf_tracker_internal_df[(spf_tracker_internal_df['p_value_avg_price'] >= 0.05) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['spf_name'] != target_spf) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['coeff_avg_price'] > 0)].spf_name.tolist()
  
  intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_WD = spf_tracker_internal_df[(spf_tracker_internal_df['p_value_WD'] < 0.05) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['spf_name'] != target_spf) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_internal_df['coeff_WD'] > 0)].spf_name.tolist()
  
  # Add shortlisting flags
  spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_price'] = spf_tracker_internal_df['spf_name'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price else 0)
  spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_wd'] = spf_tracker_internal_df['spf_name'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_WD else 0)
  spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_both'] = spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_price'] * spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_wd'] # set 1 only for both shortlist
  spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_any'] = spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_price'] + spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_wd']
  spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_any'] = spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_any'].apply(lambda x: min(x, 1)) # set 1 for either shortlist
  
  # Add to main tracker
  int_comp_tracker_master_df = pd.concat([int_comp_tracker_master_df, spf_tracker_internal_df.copy(deep=True)])
  
  if target_spf in spf_logs:
    print("***************INTERNAL*****************")
    print(ic_ols_fit.summary())
    print(f"Intm. shortlist for price: {intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price}")
    print(f"Intm. shortlist for WD: {intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_WD}")
    print(f"Common for comp among price and WD: {spf_tracker_internal_df[spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_both']==1].spf_name.tolist()}")
    print(f"Comp present in either price or WD: {spf_tracker_internal_df[spf_tracker_internal_df['sl_any']==1].spf_name.tolist()}")
  
  corr_tracker_df = pd.DataFrame(corr_tracker)
  # Shortlist competitor SPFs where sl_any=1
  intm_shortlisted_spfs = spf_tracker_internal_df[spf_tracker_internal_df.sl_any==1].spf_name.tolist()
  # If there is no shortlisted SPF, take the first SPF having highest price-volume correlation from intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price_rem list
  if len(intm_shortlisted_spfs) != 0:
    print(f"Competition found from p-values: {len(intm_shortlisted_spfs)}")
    intm_shortlisted_spfs = corr_tracker_df[corr_tracker_df.spf.isin(intm_shortlisted_spfs)].sort_values(by='corr', ascending=False).spf.tolist()
    intm_shortlisted_spfs.extend([comp_spf for comp_spf in intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price_rem if comp_spf not in intm_shortlisted_spfs])
  else:
    print(f"Competition found from p-values: {len(intm_shortlisted_spfs)}")
    intm_shortlisted_spfs = corr_tracker_df[corr_tracker_df.spf.isin(intm_shortlisted_spfs_for_price_rem)].sort_values(by='corr', ascending=False).spf.tolist()
  
  # Shortlist based on adjusted r-square
  temp_tgt_spf = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][['year', 'week', 'Sales_Volume']].copy(deep=True)
  # Take log of Sales Volume
  temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'] = temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x==0 else np.log(x))
  temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.rename(columns={'Sales_Volume': 'log_Sales_Volume'})
  
  # Keep adding variables till the adjusted r-square is improving
  final_shortlist_comps = list()
  
  if len(intm_shortlisted_spfs) != 0:
    # Add first spf based on correlation
    first_comp_spf = intm_shortlisted_spfs[0]
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(spf_dataframe_dict[first_comp_spf][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
        .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_spf}'})
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_spf}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_spf}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_spf}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    final_shortlist_comps.append(first_comp_spf)
  
  # Get baseline adj r-square
  X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
  Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
  X = sm.add_constant(X)
  ic_ols_fit_ft = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
  adj_rsq = ic_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj
  
  for comp_spf in intm_shortlisted_spfs[1:]:
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(spf_dataframe_dict[comp_spf][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
      .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'})
    
    # Take log of the prices
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    
    # Regress to see the if adjusted r-square improves
    X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
    Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    ic_ols_fit_ft = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
    # If adj r-square is not improving, then discard the competition
    if ic_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj <= adj_rsq:
      temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.drop([f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_spf}'], axis=1)
    else:
      final_shortlist_comps.append(comp_spf)
      adj_rsq = ic_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj
    if target_spf in spf_logs:
      print(adj_rsq)
    
  # If the shortlisted SPFs are > 10, then pick top 10 based on volume-price correlation
  top_10_sl_int_spfs = final_shortlist_comps[:10]
    
  # Merge the shortlisted SPFs Avg_Price into target SPF dataframe and create price index
  for i, spf in enumerate(top_10_sl_int_spfs):
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Name"] = spf
    
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].merge(spf_dataframe_dict[spf][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price','Weighted_Distribution']].rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'Avg_Price_{spf}','Weighted_Distribution' : f'Weighted_Distribution_{spf}'}),on=['year', 'week'], how='left')
    
    # setting WD to nan for spf where WD is insignificant
    if ((int_comp_tracker_master_df[(int_comp_tracker_master_df['target_spf']==target_spf) & (int_comp_tracker_master_df['spf_name']==spf)]['sl_wd'].iloc[0]==1)) :
      
      spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f'Weighted_Distribution_{spf}']
    else :
      # setting WD to nan
      spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = np.nan


    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Price_Index"] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf]['Avg_Price']/spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f'Avg_Price_{spf}']
    
    # Drop comp avg price and comp WD
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].drop(f'Avg_Price_{spf}', axis=1, inplace=True)
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].drop(f'Weighted_Distribution_{spf}', axis=1, inplace=True)
  
  # In case there aren't 10 SPFs, based on how many less are there, add comp columns and fill with Nan
  for j in range(len(top_10_sl_int_spfs),10):
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Name"] = np.nan
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Price_Index"] = np.nan
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"INTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = np.nan

# Identifying external competitors
for target_spf in spf_dataframe_dict:
  print(f"\n\nTarget SPF: {target_spf}")
  
  ########################################## External competition identification ########################################
  temp_tgt_spf = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][['year', 'week', 'Sales_Volume']].copy(deep=True)
  
  # Track comp prods
  #comp_prod_list = dict()
  
  # Track correlation 
  corr_tracker = list()
  
  # For OLS, we need num_obs > num_features, hence we will restrict num features to be 80% of observations. We will pick top 80% based on market share
  ext_comp_superset = comp_supersets['external']
  ext_comps_for_stage_1 = min(len(ext_comp_superset), int(len(temp_tgt_spf) * 0.4))
  
  for i, comp_prod in enumerate(ext_comp_superset[:ext_comps_for_stage_1]):
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price', 'Weighted_Distribution']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
      .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}',
                      'Weighted_Distribution': f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}'})
    
    # Calculate correlation (to be used as last step to shortlist)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    corr, _ = pearsonr(temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'], temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'])
    corr_tracker.append({
      'prod': comp_prod,
      'corr': corr
    })
    
    # Take log of the prices
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    #comp_prod_list[i+1] = comp_prod # counter starts from 1 to account for constant term later on
    
  # Take log of Sales Volume
  temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'] = temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x==0 else np.log(x))
  temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.rename(columns={'Sales_Volume': 'log_Sales_Volume'})
  
  # Regress on the logged comp prices to predict logged sales volume
  X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
  Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
  X = sm.add_constant(X)
  ec_ols_fit = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
  
  # Create spf-wise p-values for both Avg price and WD
  spf_tracker_external = list()
  for col_index in range(1, len(X.columns)):
    temp_prod_details = dict()
    cprod_name = X.columns[col_index]
    if 'Avg_Price' in cprod_name:
      temp_prod_details['prod_name'] = cprod_name[14:]
      temp_prod_details['p_value_avg_price'] = ec_ols_fit.pvalues[col_index]
      temp_prod_details['coeff_avg_price'] = ec_ols_fit.params[col_index]
    elif 'Weighted_Distribution' in cprod_name:
      temp_prod_details['prod_name'] = cprod_name[26:]
      temp_prod_details['p_value_WD'] = ec_ols_fit.pvalues[col_index]
      temp_prod_details['coeff_WD'] = ec_ols_fit.params[col_index]
#     temp_prod_details['p-value'] = ec_ols_fit.pvalues[col_index]
#     temp_prod_details['coeff'] = ec_ols_fit.params[col_index]
    spf_tracker_external.append(deepcopy(temp_prod_details))
  
  spf_tracker_external_df = pd.DataFrame(spf_tracker_external)
  spf_tracker_external_df.insert(0, 'target_spf', target_spf)
  spf_tracker_external_df = spf_tracker_external_df.groupby(['target_spf', 'prod_name'], as_index=False).sum()
   
  intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price = spf_tracker_external_df[(spf_tracker_external_df['p_value_avg_price'] < 0.05) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_external_df['coeff_avg_price'] > 0)].prod_name.tolist()
  
  # pick the ones with p-value more than or equal to 0.05 but with +ve coeff
  intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price_rem = spf_tracker_external_df[(spf_tracker_external_df['p_value_avg_price'] >= 0.05) &
                                                                 (spf_tracker_external_df['coeff_avg_price'] > 0)].prod_name.tolist()
  
  intm_shortlisted_prods_for_WD = spf_tracker_external_df[(spf_tracker_external_df['p_value_WD'] < 0.05) &
                                                   (spf_tracker_external_df['coeff_WD'] > 0)].prod_name.tolist()
  
  # Add shortlisting flags
  spf_tracker_external_df['sl_price'] = spf_tracker_external_df['prod_name'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price else 0)
  spf_tracker_external_df['sl_wd'] = spf_tracker_external_df['prod_name'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x in intm_shortlisted_prods_for_WD else 0)
  spf_tracker_external_df['sl_both'] = spf_tracker_external_df['sl_price']*spf_tracker_external_df['sl_wd'] # set 1 only for both shortlist
  spf_tracker_external_df['sl_any'] = spf_tracker_external_df['sl_price'] + spf_tracker_external_df['sl_wd']
  spf_tracker_external_df['sl_any'] = spf_tracker_external_df['sl_any'].apply(lambda x: min(x, 1)) # set 1 for either shortlist
  
  # Add to main tracker
  ext_comp_tracker_master_df = pd.concat([ext_comp_tracker_master_df, spf_tracker_external_df.copy(deep=True)])
  
  if target_spf in spf_logs:
    print("***************EXTERNAL*****************")
    print(ec_ols_fit.summary())
    print(f"Intm. shortlist for price: {intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price}")
    print(f"Intm. shortlist for WD: {intm_shortlisted_prods_for_WD}")
    print(f"Common for comp among price and WD: {spf_tracker_external_df[spf_tracker_external_df['sl_both']==1].prod_name.tolist()}")
    print(f"Comp present in either price or WD: {spf_tracker_external_df[spf_tracker_external_df['sl_any']==1].prod_name.tolist()}")
    
  corr_tracker_df = pd.DataFrame(corr_tracker)
  # Shortlist competitor prods where sl_any=1
  intm_shortlisted_prods = spf_tracker_external_df[spf_tracker_external_df.sl_any==1].prod_name.tolist()
  # If there is no shortlisted comp prod, take the first SPF having highest price-volume correlation from intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price_rem list
  if len(intm_shortlisted_prods) != 0:
    print(f"Competition found from p-values: {len(intm_shortlisted_prods)}")
    intm_shortlisted_prods = corr_tracker_df[corr_tracker_df['prod'].isin(intm_shortlisted_prods)].sort_values(by='corr', ascending=False)['prod'].tolist()
    intm_shortlisted_prods.extend([comp_prod for comp_prod in intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price_rem if comp_prod not in intm_shortlisted_prods])
  else:
    print(f"Competition found from p-values: {len(intm_shortlisted_prods)}")
    intm_shortlisted_prods = corr_tracker_df[corr_tracker_df['prod'].isin(intm_shortlisted_prods_for_price_rem)].sort_values(by='corr', ascending=False)['prod'].tolist()
  
  # Shortlist based on adjusted r-square
  temp_tgt_spf = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][['year', 'week', 'Sales_Volume']].copy(deep=True)
  # Take log of Sales Volume
  temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'] = temp_tgt_spf['Sales_Volume'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x==0 else np.log(x))
  temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.rename(columns={'Sales_Volume': 'log_Sales_Volume'})
  
  # Keep adding variables till the adjusted r-square is improving
  final_shortlist_comps = list()
  
  if len(intm_shortlisted_prods) != 0:
    # Add first spf based on correlation
    first_comp_prod = intm_shortlisted_prods[0]
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(comp_prod_dataframe_dict[first_comp_prod][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
        .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_prod}'})
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_prod}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_prod}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{first_comp_prod}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    final_shortlist_comps.append(first_comp_prod)
  
  # Get baseline adj r-square
  X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
  Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
  X = sm.add_constant(X)
  ec_ols_fit_ft = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
  adj_rsq = ec_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj
  
  for comp_prod in intm_shortlisted_prods[1:]:
    temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.merge(comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price']], on=['year', 'week'], how='left') \
      .rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'})
    
    # Take log of the prices
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'].fillna(0, inplace=True)
    temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'] = temp_tgt_spf[f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'].apply(lambda x: 0 if (x==0 or math.isnan(x)) else np.log(x))
    
    # Regress to see the if adjusted r-square improves
    X = temp_tgt_spf.drop(['year', 'week', 'log_Sales_Volume'], axis=1)
    Y = temp_tgt_spf['log_Sales_Volume']
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    ec_ols_fit_ft = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()
    # If adj r-square is not improving, then discard the competition
    if ec_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj <= adj_rsq:
      temp_tgt_spf = temp_tgt_spf.drop([f'log_Avg_Price_{comp_prod}'], axis=1)
    else:
      final_shortlist_comps.append(comp_prod)
      adj_rsq = ec_ols_fit_ft.rsquared_adj
  
  # If the shortlisted comp prods are > 10, then pick top 10 based on volume-price correlation
  top_10_sl_ext_prods = final_shortlist_comps[:10]
  

  # Merge the shortlisted comp prods Avg_Price into target SPF dataframe and create price index
  for i, comp_prod in enumerate(top_10_sl_ext_prods):
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Name"] = comp_prod
    
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].merge(comp_prod_dataframe_dict[comp_prod][['year', 'week', 'Avg_Price','Weighted_Distribution']].rename(columns={'Avg_Price': f'Avg_Price_{comp_prod}','Weighted_Distribution' : f'Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}'}),on=['year', 'week'], how='left')
    
    # setting WD to nan for spf where WD is insignificant
    if ((ext_comp_tracker_master_df[(ext_comp_tracker_master_df['target_spf']==target_spf) & (ext_comp_tracker_master_df['prod_name']==comp_prod)]['sl_wd'].iloc[0]==1)) :
      
      spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f'Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}']
    else :
      # setting WD to nan
      spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = np.nan
    
    # Calculate price index
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{i+1}_Price_Index"] = spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf]['Avg_Price']/spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f'Avg_Price_{comp_prod}']
    
    # Drop comp avg price
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].drop(f'Avg_Price_{comp_prod}', axis=1, inplace=True)
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf].drop(f'Weighted_Distribution_{comp_prod}', axis=1, inplace=True)
  
  # In case there aren't 10 comp prods, based on how many less are there, add comp columns and fill with Nan
  for j in range(len(top_10_sl_ext_prods),10):
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Name"] = np.nan
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Price_Index"] = np.nan
    spf_dataframe_dict[target_spf][f"EXTERNAL_COMP_{j+1}_Weighted_Distribution"] = np.nan

unilever_final_df_2 = pd.DataFrame()

  unilever_final_df_2 = pd.concat([unilever_final_df_2, spf_dataframe_dict[spf]])

unilever_final_df_2 = unilever_final_df_2.drop_duplicates()

import math
# Keep track of availibility of competitors for all the spfs
def check_nan(x):
  if math.isnan(x):
    return 0
  return 1
spf_comp_summary = unilever_final_df[['country', 'category', 'company', 'spf_desc']].copy()
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_1'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_2'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_3'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_4'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_4_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_5'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_5_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_6'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_6_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_7'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_7_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_8'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_8_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_9'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_9_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_internal_comp_10'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_10_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)

spf_comp_summary['has_external_comp_1'] = unilever_final_df.EXTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)
spf_comp_summary['has_external_comp_2'] = unilever_final_df.EXTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)

spf_comp_summary['has_external_comp_10'] = unilever_final_df.EXTERNAL_COMP_10_Price_Index.apply(check_nan)

spf_comp_summary = spf_comp_summary.groupby(['country', 'category', 'company', 'spf_desc'], as_index=False).sum()
spf_comp_summary['total_weeks'] = unilever_final_df.groupby('spf_desc', as_index=False)['spf_desc'].count()

from sklearn.metrics import r2_score

def rsquared(y_true, y_pred):
  slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, std_err = scipy.stats.linregress(y_true, y_pred)
  rsq=r_value**2
  #mape=np.mean(np.abs((y_pred - y_true) / y_pred))
  return rsq

def check_max_range(coeff, coeff_range):
    if coeff < coeff_range[0]:
        return coeff_range[0]
    elif coeff > coeff_range[1]:
        return coeff_range[1]
    return coeff

def update_coeff(coeff, corr, col, coeff_range, lrn_rt):
    if coeff==0:
      coeff == 0
    else :
      if corr.loc[col] > 0:
          coeff = np.round(coeff + (corr.loc[col]**2) * lrn_rt * abs(abs(coeff) - abs(coeff_range[1])), 2)
      elif corr.loc[col] < 0:
          coeff = np.round(coeff - (corr.loc[col]**2) * lrn_rt * abs(abs(coeff_range[0]) - abs(coeff)), 2)
    
    coeff = check_max_range(coeff, coeff_range)
    return coeff
#corr_x, corr_y, corr_z = [], [], []

#def update_priors(df, x_co, y_co, z_co, mu_intercept, x_range, y_range, z_range):
def update_priors(df, var_coef_dict, mu_intercept, actual, var_range_dict,lrn_rt):
  
    # Print Old coeffs
    print(f"Old Coeffs: {var_coef_dict}\nmu_intercept: {mu_intercept}")
    
    def calculate_predicted(var_coef_dict, row):
      predicted = 0
      for var in var_coef_dict:
        predicted += var_coef_dict[var]*row[var]
      return predicted
      
    df['predicted'] = df.apply(lambda x: calculate_predicted(var_coef_dict, x), axis=1)
    df['predicted'] += mu_intercept
    
    #df['predicted'] = (x_co * df.x_data) + (y_co * df.y_data) + (z_co * df.z_data) + mu_intercept
    df['error'] = df[actual] - df['predicted']
    
    mu_intercept = mu_intercept + (np.nanmean(df[actual]) - np.nanmean(df['predicted'])) * lrn_rt
    
    corr_df = df.corr(method='pearson')['error']
    corr_df.fillna(0, inplace=True)
    
    print("Correlations\n", corr_df)
    
#     corr_x.append(corr_df.x_data)
#     corr_y.append(corr_df.y_data)
#     corr_z.append(corr_df.z_data)
    
    new_var_coef_dict = dict()
    for var in var_coef_dict:
      new_var_coef_dict[var] = update_coeff(var_coef_dict[var], corr_df, var, var_range_dict[var],lrn_rt)
    
#     x_co = update_coeff(x_co, corr_df, 'x_data', x_range)
#     y_co = update_coeff(y_co, corr_df, 'y_data', y_range)
#     z_co = update_coeff(z_co, corr_df, 'z_data', z_range)
    
    df['predicted'] = df.apply(lambda x: calculate_predicted(new_var_coef_dict, x), axis=1)
    df['predicted'] += mu_intercept
    
    #df['predicted'] = (x_co * df.x_data) + (y_co * df.y_data) + (z_co * df.z_data) + mu_intercept
    df['error'] = df[actual] - df['predicted']
    
    rsq = rsquared(np.exp(df[actual]), np.exp(df['predicted']))
    tdf = df[df[actual]!=0] # create temp df having non-zero actual so as to calculate MAPE
    mape = np.mean(np.abs((np.exp(tdf[actual]) - np.exp(tdf['predicted'])))/np.abs(np.exp(tdf[actual])))
    
    return new_var_coef_dict, mu_intercept, rsq, mape

from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

def run_model_OLS(test_df, var_range_dict_global, modelling_cols, target, lrn_rt):
  
  global_results = list()
  #for spf in ['REX FEMALE AP AERO MAXPRO 150ML']:
  for spf in test_df.spf_desc.unique():
    print(f"Running for spf: {spf}")
    test_spf_df = test_df[test_df.spf_desc==spf][modelling_cols].copy()
    results = []
    
    # Get initial coeffs initialization by using OLS
    var_coef_dict = dict()
    X, y = test_spf_df.drop(target, axis=1), test_spf_df[target]
    lr = LinearRegression().fit(X, y)
    
    for coef, val in zip(var_range_dict_global, lr.coef_):
      var_coef_dict[coef] = val
    
    mu_intercept = lr.intercept_
    #mu_intercept = 0
    var_range_dict = deepcopy(var_range_dict_global)

    for i in range(200):
        var_coef_dict, mu_intercept, rsq, mape = update_priors(test_spf_df, var_coef_dict, mu_intercept, target, var_range_dict,lrn_rt)
        print("New Coeffs: ", var_coef_dict, mu_intercept)
        print("R_square: ", round(rsq, 3))
        print("Mape: ", round(mape, 3), "\n")

        results_dict = deepcopy(var_coef_dict)
        results_dict.update({
          'mu_intercept': mu_intercept,
          'R_square': round(rsq, 3),
           'Mape': round(mape, 3) 
        })

        results.append(deepcopy(results_dict))

    glob_res = dict()
    glob_res['spf_desc'] = spf
    glob_res['lrn_rt']=lrn_rt                             # added on 17/02/2022
    glob_res['modeling']='OLS'                            # added on 17/02/2022
    results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
    #glob_res.update(results_df.sort_values(by='R_square', ascending=False).head(1).to_dict(orient='records')[0])
    glob_res.update(results_df.sort_values(by='Mape').head(1).to_dict(orient='records')[0])

    global_results.append(deepcopy(glob_res))

  return pd.DataFrame(global_results)

Concatenatinating the OLS and Manual Modeling results¶

In [0]:
results_df_total= pd.concat([results_df_OLS,results_df_manual_init],axis=0)
In [0]:
results_df=pd.DataFrame(columns=results_df_total.columns)

for i in results_df_total.spf_desc.unique():
    
  temp=results_df_total[results_df_total.spf_desc==i]
  temp_rsqr_grt_65 = temp[temp.R_square>=0.65]
  
  if(temp_rsqr_grt_65.shape[0]!=0):
    temp_rsqr_grt_65_mape_less_30=temp_rsqr_grt_65[temp_rsqr_grt_65.Mape<=0.30]
    if(temp_rsqr_grt_65_mape_less_30.shape[0]!=0):
      a=temp_rsqr_grt_65_mape_less_30.loc[temp_rsqr_grt_65_mape_less_30['R_square']== temp_rsqr_grt_65_mape_less_30['R_square'].max()].head(1)
      results_df=pd.concat([results_df,a],axis=0)
    else:
      a=temp_rsqr_grt_65.loc[temp_rsqr_grt_65['Mape']==temp_rsqr_grt_65['Mape'].min()].head(1)
      results_df=pd.concat([results_df,a],axis=0)
  else:
    temp_mape_less_30=temp[temp['Mape']<=0.30]
    
    if(temp_mape_less_30.shape[0]!=0):
      a=temp_mape_less_30.loc[temp_mape_less_30['R_square']==temp_mape_less_30['R_square'].max()].head(1)
      results_df=pd.concat([results_df,a],axis=0)
    else:
      a=temp.loc[temp['Mape']==temp['Mape'].min()].head(1)
      results_df=pd.concat([results_df,a],axis=0)

import pymc3 as pm
import arviz as az
In [0]:
# implmenting HBR
def get_prior(prior_name, prior_type, lower, upper, mu=None, sigma=None, shape=1):
    if prior_type == 'UNIFORM':
        prior = pm.Uniform(prior_name, lower=lower, upper=upper, shape=shape)
    elif prior_type == 'NORMAL':
        bounded_normal = pm.Bound(pm.Normal, lower=lower, upper=upper)
        prior = bounded_normal(prior_name, mu=mu, \
                                        sigma=sigma, shape=shape)
    else:
        pass 
    return prior

            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_2_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_2_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_3_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_3_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_4_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_4_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_5_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_5_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_6_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_6_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_7_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_7_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_8_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_8_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_9_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_9_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + log_EXTERNAL_COMP_10_Weighted_Distribution_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_10_Weighted_Distribution']\
            + Seasonality_slope[spfs_idx] * test_df['Seasonality']
        
        # Model error:
        sigma_1 = pm.Exponential('sigma_1',1.0)
        y = pm.Normal('y', sls_volume, sigma=sigma_1, observed=test_df['log_Sales_Volume'])
        
        
        if run_model=='Y':     
          trace_dict = {}
          with model_hbr:
              trace_dict['hierarch'] = pm.sample(draws=2000, tune=500, \
                                                  target_accept=0.95)

#         with open(COUNTRY.lower()+'_trace.pkl', 'wb') as country_model_pickle:
#             pkl.dump({'model': model_hbr, 'trace': trace_dict['hierarch']}, country_model_pickle)
          summary = az.summary(trace_dict['hierarch'])
        return summary

def find_index(index_col_name, data):
    unique_idx = data[index_col_name].unique()
    n_idx = data[index_col_name].nunique()
    idx = pd.Index(unique_idx).get_indexer(data[index_col_name])
    return unique_idx, n_idx, idx
  
def get_params(keys, values):
    params = dict(zip(keys, values))
    return params
  
def get_mape(y_act, y_pred):
    '''Function calclates mean absolute percentage error (MAPE)'''
    y_act, y_pred = np.asarray(y_act), np.asarray(y_pred)
    return np.mean(np.abs((np.exp(y_act) - np.exp(y_pred)))/np.abs(np.exp(y_act)))
  
def rsquared(y_true, y_pred):
  slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, std_err = scipy.stats.linregress(y_true, y_pred)
  rsq=r_value**2
  #mape=np.mean(np.abs((y_pred - y_true) / y_pred))
  return rsq
  
def get_prediction(data, features, series, df_hbr):
    prediction_result = pd.DataFrame()
    df_hbr['ERROR'] = 0
    for s in series:
        coeff_list = df_hbr[df_hbr['spf_desc']==s][features].to_numpy()
        input_features = data[data['spf_desc']==s][features]
        prediction = input_features.dot(coeff_list.transpose().reshape(-1,1))
        series_result = pd.DataFrame()
        series_result['PREDICTION'] = prediction[0]
        series_result['ACTUAL'] = data[data['spf_desc']==s]['log_Sales_Volume'] 
        df_hbr.loc[df_hbr['spf_desc']==s,'ERROR'] = series_result['ACTUAL'].mean() - series_result['PREDICTION'].mean()
#         series_result['PREDICTION'] = series_result['PREDICTION']+(series_result['ACTUAL'].mean() - series_result['PREDICTION'].mean())
        series_result_mape = series_result[series_result['ACTUAL']!=0]
        series_result['MAPE']=get_mape(series_result_mape['ACTUAL'], series_result_mape['PREDICTION'])
        series_result['R_square'] = rsquared(series_result['ACTUAL'], series_result['PREDICTION'])
        series_result['DATE'] = data[data['spf_desc']==s]['date']
        series_result['spf_desc']=s        
        prediction_result = pd.concat([prediction_result,series_result], axis=0) 
    return prediction_result.reset_index(drop=True), df_hbr
  

  
  

spfs, n_spfs, spfs_idx = find_index('spf_desc', test_df)

# Add predicted value for above data
def get_predicted(x):
  coeff_dict = results_df[results_df.spf_desc==x['spf_desc']].to_dict(orient='records')[0]
  predval = 0
  
  for mcol in modelling_cols:
    if mcol != 'log_Sales_Volume':
      predval += x[mcol]*coeff_dict[mcol]
  
  predval += coeff_dict['mu_intercept']
  return predval
  
#   predval += x['log_Base_Price']*coeff_dict['log_Base_Price'] + x['TPR']*coeff_dict['TPR'] + x['log_Weighted_Distribution']*coeff_dict['log_Weighted_Distribution'] + \
#     x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_INTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index'] + x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_INTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index'] + x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_INTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index'] + x['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_1_Price_Index'] + \
#   x['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_2_Price_Index'] + x['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index']*coeff_dict['log_EXTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index'] + x['Seasonality']*coeff_dict['Seasonality'] + x['Covid']*coeff_dict['Covid'] + coeff_dict['mu_intercept'] + x['Lockdown Stockpiling']*coeff_dict['Lockdown Stockpiling']
#   #x['Lockdown Stockpiling']*coeff_dict['Lockdown Stockpiling'] + coeff_dict['mu_intercept'] #+ x['Covid']*coeff_dict['Covid']
  #return predval

test_df['predicted_val'] = test_df.apply(get_predicted, axis=1)

# Extract their sales volume for last 52 weeks
# internal comps
internal_comps_volume = dict()
for ic in internal_comp_set:
  temp_df = unilever_final_df[unilever_final_df.spf_desc==ic].sort_values(by=['year', 'week'], ascending=False).head(52).copy()
  internal_comps_volume[ic] = temp_df.Sales_Volume.sum()

# external comps
external_comps_volume = dict()
for ec in external_comp_set:
  temp_df = comp_df[comp_df.product_desc==ec].sort_values(by=['year', 'week'], ascending=False).head(52).copy()
  external_comps_volume[ec] = temp_df.Sales_Volume.sum()

# Add comp_sales value
def get_int_comp_sales(x):
  try:
    if math.isnan(x):
      return 0
  except:
    return internal_comps_volume[x]

def get_ext_comp_sales(x):
  try:
    if math.isnan(x):
      return 0
  except TypeError:
    return external_comps_volume[x]

unilever_final_df['internal_comp1_sv'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_1_Name.apply(get_int_comp_sales)
unilever_final_df['internal_comp2_sv'] = unilever_final_df.INTERNAL_COMP_2_Name.apply(get_int_comp_sales)

                    + x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_3_Price_Index']*x['internal_comp3_sv'] + x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_4_Price_Index']*x['internal_comp4_sv'] + x['log_INTERNAL_COMP_5_Price_Index']*x['internal_comp5_sv']
